04/11/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- In a move intended to ease overcrowding in jails, the justice ministry has drafted a list of 240 prisoners eligible for amnesty, the <I>Albanian Daily News</I> reported Thursday (4 November).
Justice Minister Fatmir Xhafa said the list would be submitted to President Alfred Moisiu, who is expected to grant amnesties as he marks the end-of-year holidays.
All those involved have less than a year left to serve.
Xhafa also proposed the prisoners to be given the chance to work.
(Albanian Daily News - 04/11/04)
